Habitat and natural history. At the type locality, males were reported to frequent leaf litter and small streams in forests, and were heard vocalising especially on nights with clear skies ( 14 July–08 August ). Tadpoles allocated to this species were collected from amongst rocks at the base of a waterfall of a small stream (
Fei et al. 2009
), but the authors did not justify how they identified the tadpoles.
